From: Gemini PDA Mainline Project <noreply@example.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 03:12:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 30/30] arm64: dts: mediatek: mt6797: add display mutex

Describe the MT6797 display hardware mutex. It belongs to the MM power
domain and has no independent clock. Expose the first two stream-EOF GCE
events used by the display paths and the command-engine client window for
the 0x1401xxxx subsystem selector.

The provider is safe to bind before DRM consumers are described: probe only
maps the register aperture and records the optional GCE tuple.

Signed-off-by: Gemini PDA Mainline Project <noreply@example.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797.dtsi | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797.dtsi
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797.dtsi
@@ -540,6 +540,16 @@ mmsys: syscon@14000000 {
 		#clock-cells = <1>;
 	};
 
+	mutex: mutex@1401f000 {
+		compatible = "mediatek,mt6797-disp-mutex";
+		reg = <0 0x1401f000 0 0x1000>;
+		interrupts = <GIC_SPI 202 IRQ_TYPE_LEVEL_LOW>;
+		power-domains = <&scpsys MT6797_POWER_DOMAIN_MM>;
+		mediatek,gce-events = <CMDQ_EVENT_MUTEX0_STREAM_EOF>,
+				      <CMDQ_EVENT_MUTEX1_STREAM_EOF>;
+		mediatek,gce-client-reg = <&gce SUBSYS_1401XXXX 0xf000 0x1000>;
+	};
+
 	larb0: larb@14020000 {
 		compatible = "mediatek,mt6797-smi-larb";
 		reg = <0 0x14020000 0 0x1000>;
-- 
